<p><strong>Black Bow</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Bows" href="/Bows" target="">Bow</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Black Bow</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for Bow Builds.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Longbow carved from black wood to resemble a blade. One of the most difficult bows to master.</em></p> 
 <p><em>The blade-like body of the bow is light and cuts through the air.<br>Though a longbow, it can be wielded similarly to a shortbow.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Black Bow in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Black Bow weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Found on a corpse on a rooftop, in the area to the north east of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=3248&amp;lat=-102.114583&amp;lng=115.524421&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=3248&amp;lat=-102.114583&amp;lng=115.524421&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Avenue Balcony</a> site of grace, in the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Leyndell Royal Capital (Legacy Dungeon)" href="/Leyndell+Royal+Capital+(Legacy+Dungeon)">Leyndell, Royal Capital</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=3843&amp;lat=-101.054687&amp;lng=115.876041&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=3843&amp;lat=-101.054687&amp;lng=115.876041&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Black Bow Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Barrage" href="/Barrage" target="">Barrage</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon&nbsp;cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Black Bow</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Acts similarly to a Shortbow, allowing you to jump and shoot and shoot again immediately upon landing.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;200</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
