				<li id="16640081" class="cmnt-root" data="288" data-d="1650471429000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578301/Black-Bow" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">20 Apr 2022 12:17</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16640081" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I wanted to type this up for anyone considering a bow build...<br/><br/>I&apos;ve been a bow-main since release, and I see a lot of misinformation about them; discouraging others from giving them a try. I want to set things straight. BOWS. ARE. VIABLE... kinda. They&apos;re more viable during NG+, since you&apos;ll be more established. I&apos;ll be honest, bows are no where near as powerful as melee weapons. The scaling on them is terrible and the skills for bows aren&apos;t that great either. Additionally, getting to the bosses, going through mobs, can be difficult with bow-only. However, bows can still hold their own. It just takes work.<br/><br/>I&apos;m commenting this on the Black Bow for a reason. You&apos;ve probably been told that this is the best bow in the game; this is true. This bow has the mechanics of a light bow (i.e. enhanced jump-shot, landing-shot, sprint-shot, roll-shot, and the Barrage skill), and the damage of a regular bow. The Black Bow will be the bow that will take you through most of the game, and most of the bosses. If you want to use this bow, I HIGHLY recommend learning these mechanics and making them second-nature. As for other bows, you&apos;ll want to have at least two more for different situations. In some cases you&apos;ll want to use Mighty Shot; others, Rain of Arrows. I recommend either the Pulley Bow, Albinauric Bow, or Composite Bow (if you want to stick to light-mechanics). Quick tip about the Composite Light Bow: The scaling is actually D/D (not E/D), making this the best lightbow for str/dex builds (which I recommend building). Back to Black Bow. The barrage skill is nice. The speed at which it shoots arrows makes up for the damage decrease (lessened even more by Shard of Alexander (even beats Might Shot)); but don&apos;t rely only on it. Like I said, get down the mechanics, as they&apos;re a lot more important. <br/><br/>I see a lot of misinformation about talismans, especially. Let me state that I&apos;ve tested each and every one of these; I know what I&apos;m talking about here. If I&apos;m wrong, though, let me know in the comments, please. The four talismans, I recommend: Arrow&apos;s Sting, Blue Dancer Charm, Ritual Sword, and Shard of Alexander. Each one of these will give a damage increase. If you don&apos;t want to keep Blue Dancer, Ritual Sword, or Shard, I recommend Green Turtle, Arrow&apos;s Reach, and/or Spear Talisman (yes, it actually affects bows). CLAW TALISMAN DOES NOT AFFECT BOWS. I see a lot of people saying to equip Claw Talisman, but do not! As much as I wish it increased the jump attacks, it doesn&apos;t. <br/><br/>Lastly, make sure to allocate just enough points into Faith to be able to use Golden Vow and Flame, Give Me Strength! <br/><br/>Quick notes:<br/>- Barrage deals more damage than Mighty Shot, using this setup, in the time it takes to shoot a Might Shot.<br/>- Roll-shot is AMAZING!<br/>- To do a landing-shot, immediately after you land from a jump-shot, fire again!<br/>- Again, CLAW TALI DOES NOT WORK ON BOWS!<br/>- Don&apos;t rely only on Bleed Arrows; use regular arrows, as well.<br/>- You can buy regular arrows (the 2nd strongest raw damage arrow) from the merchant at Church of Elleh.<br/>- Instead of farming sheep, kill the Bell Bearing Hunter. You&apos;ll be able to buy thin bones at the Roundtable. <br/><br/>Hope this helps! I will keep checking in on this post to answer any questions, if needed.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16640081" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16640081" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">16</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>291</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>3</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16640081"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16640081" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16640081"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
