				<li id="16506990" class="cmnt-root" data="21" data-d="1647253761000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><a class="comment-username" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=128451" rel="nofollow"  target="_blank" style="color: #;">Silves</a></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578301/Black-Bow" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">14 Mar 2022 06:29</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16506990" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This bow is my favourite. Deals good damage if you jump, shoot and after landing immediately press attack button while moving — the player will shoot as if after rolling, meaning you can do 2 quick bow attacks. These attacks are much faster than just shooting while standing still or moving on the ground. It could be a bug, but I couldn&apos;t do the same with Albinauric and Serpent bows. So, as i said: Jump -&gt; Shoot -&gt; Hold down the stick/wasd to move in any direction (works like charm if moving forward -&gt; Upon landing shoot again -&gt; Voila, two rapid bow shots.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16506990" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16506990" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>25</p><i cla