				<li id="16491776" class="cmnt-root" data="55" data-d="1646992057000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578301/Black-Bow" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">11 Mar 2022 04:47</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16491776" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Softcaps for damage for this bow at +10 seem to be 36 STR (54 virtual) and 58 DEX for 319 AR; No Damage enhancing runes were used, standard 20 cost arrows.  Strength leveling falls off hard beyond this point while DEX drops to 2 points spread over 3 levels for a while rather than 1 point per level.  Dex is still worth leveling, just less.<br/><br/>It&apos;s AR is almost exactly in the middle of Long Bow and Short Bow but has all the benefits of both the light and standard bow classes while on foot.<br/><br/>Very solid PvP bow and decent weapon for &apos;bow only&apos; runs against bosses.  Has a mediocre weapon art which takes away from it&apos;s PvP potential but has the Long Bow range with the running, dodge, quick draw, and roll attacks of the Short Bow.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16491776" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16491776" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="